        resumableInfo -
        Returns:
        True if both HttpResumableInfo are compatible (size, chunk size, total number of chunks, identifier and current chunk vs max chunk number)

      • getChunkSize

        public int getChunkSize()
        The general chunk size. Using this value and resumableTotalSize you can calculate the total number of chunks. Please note that the size of the data received in the HTTP might be higher than resumableChunkSize for the last chunk for a file. Max being 2^31, preferably 2^20 (1 MB)

      • setChunkSize

        public HttpResumableInfo setChunkSize(int chunkSize)

      • getTotalSize

        public long getTotalSize()
        The total file size. Max being theoretically 2^63, but in practice being resumableChunkSize x resumableTotalChunks, therefore 2^20 x 2^31 = 2^51

      • setTotalSize

        public HttpResumableInfo setTotalSize(long totalSize)

      • getIdentifier

        public String getIdentifier()
        A unique identifier for the file contained in the request.

      • getTotalChunks

        public int getTotalChunks()
        The total number of chunks. Max being 2^31

      • getChunkNumber

        public int getChunkNumber()
        The index of the chunk in the current upload. First chunk is 1 (no base-0 counting here). Max being 2^31
